2) How many of you started a wizard to get O'kiels?<br>
3) How many of you started a wizard to get IC one day? <br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;3&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Transportation IS NOT a way to get xp. Its a way to be slightly useful in certain situations. Wizards are not broken at just 50+ they a broken through all levels and in all levels there needs to be a reason to have a wizard. At virtually all points of a wizards life any other class with signifcant dd capabilty can replace a wizard for take down factor in a xp group. What VI needs to remember is our ever so small lead (VI made it that small) in dd is quickly destroyed by those other classes other abilties (pets, healing, and what ever else). <br>
<br>
If VI wants to fix wizard for the new uber hp mobs they should do the %dmg since it doesn't give huge power bonus in old world. <br>
<br>
If however they want to fix grouping they need to give us a way to be use full (at ALL levlels) in a group that is unique to us. Not required but usefull and unique to use regardless of the level of wizard. Now given wizard get sight, ports, and dd it makes sense to keep it related to dmg. My ideas include:<br>
Reverse dmg shield (VI has heard this one for over a year)<br>
Focused dd attack through a target (kinda like rogue posion applied to a tank by a wizard)<br>
Mana leak (a bizarre idea based of reverse of intra zone ports side effects). <br>
<br>
Focus dd would be almost be a one shot reverse dmg shield. It however would be extremely mana efective (think 3 or 4 times as effective as the dd for the level). Since the spell requires the next attack to hit however the total power of the spell is reduced until the tanks get their skills. Its actual dmg would be similar to that of that levels dd spells. It could be used in normal combat or to give the tank the extra dmg needed to save the cleric from a mob.<br>
<br>
Mana leak would bleed mana from the mana used to cast ANY dd spells into other party members (intra zone ports sucks mana and such from party so this code must be in the game and is a sign and value change). At early levels not all mana would be absorbed by party members. In the mid levels it would be possible for a net party mana change of 0. Since at high levels wizards are disrupting the universe enough to rip commets from the sky it could even be possible to produce more mana for the party then the wizard used. <p><HR><TABLE BORDER="10"> <TR><TD>Gilthenos Drah'kos, 51 levels of mana powered destruction with a sick personality. Now where is my clarity?!?!</TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1849<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 7:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A quick poll... and some steam releasing.. and ideas</span><hr size=1> Actually, I honest to God started a Wizard because of the 'seekers of knowledge' aspect.  I saw Grimstaff as a wizened old man with a beard and a gnarled staff travelling to distant places for a scrap of paper in a lost library, talking to hermits on top of forbidden crags, whispering secrets from ghosts in a hidden tomb, chatting with Dragons for secrets man was not meant to know.  I saw researching spells as making your own spells, learning the technique and the power from your travels and learning.  Damage was absolutely the last thing on the list I was concerned with, I figured I'd do ok.<br>
<br>
I couldn't have possibly been more wrong. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 8:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A quick poll... and some steam releasing.. and ideas</span><hr size=1> i to started a wizard because of the mystique surrounding them in former rpg's.<br>
wizards are supposed to be fearless of a sort, going anywhere and doing anything just to gain knowledge and scribble it down in some odd handwriting it would take 100 years just to decode, much less to grasp the meaning of the words afterwards.<br>
damage was a nice addition to get xp hehe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udiison.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diison</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 3:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A quick poll... and some steam releasing.. and ideas</span><hr size=1> Started a wizard for the line in the manual (yes I bought it, shoot me =\ )<br>
<br>
'Masters of Damage'<br>
<br>
I shouldve been a rogue =(<br>
<br>
/shout Taxi *ring ring* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualyssandra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alyssandra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/01 11:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A quick poll... and some steam releasing.. and ideas</span><hr size=1> I came from an old game called Drakkar.  Where the wizard type was really a combination of wizard, enchanter and magician in EQ.  So I had a really tough time choosing but I finally decided I was interested in the aspect of being a damage dealer and yet being at the same time able to save folks in case things went bad.<br>
<br>
The one thing I do miss is being able to buff shield type spells on others which our old game allowed.  But as I said that game had one spell caster that had the attributes of the three classes I listed.  But overall despite everything I am very happy I am playing a wizard.<br>
<br>
If I had to do it all over again I still would play a wizard.<br>
<br>
Alyssandra, 55 Wizard<br>
